      "name": "Hemolysis index comparison — FDA pump bench data vs CFD predictions",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values for five flow-speed operating points are compared against hemolysis measurements drawn from a multi-site observational registry of clinical CPB procedures using the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. Across all five operating points, CFD predictions fell within 12% of the registry central estimates, with RH remaining below 1.0 in all cases. The observational cohort comprised 47 patients across three clinical sites, with pump operating conditions recorded prospectively. Detailed regression analysis confirmed monotonic sensitivity of RH to impeller tip speed, consistent with CFD-predicted trends. The strength and breadth of this dataset are cited as primary evidence supporting validation adequacy for MRL 2.",
