      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh sensitivity and discretization error assessment",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) computed across three mesh refinement levels (2.1M, 6.8M, and 18.4M elements) for the FDA pump geometry at the 6 L/min, 3500 RPM operating point. GCI for hemolysis-weighted shear stress was 3.2%, below the 5% threshold specified for MRL 2. Richardson extrapolation confirmed monotonic convergence. The fine mesh (18.4M elements) was adopted for all production runs.",
